LETTERS FROM PUBLIC: For commercial stations, does the licensee retain all written comments and suggestions received from the public, including e-mail, regarding operation of their station unless the writer requested that the correspondence not be made public or the licensee felt that it must be excluded because of the nature of its content, such as a defamatory or obscene letter? E-mail copies may be kept either on the computer or on paper.
