SECTION IV: Continued F. SPURIOUS AND HARMONIC EMISSIONS: Emissions from TV transmitters on frequencies in excess of 3 MHZ above and below the channel edges shall be attenuated at least 60 dB below the visual transmitted power.
In certain cases greater attenuation may be required to eliminate interference.
Additional emission limits for the spectrum within 3 MHZ, including the lower sideband modulation energy, are found in 73.687(a).
[See 73.687(a), 73.687(e)] 84.
