- A type of transmission used in the standard radio broadcast band at 535-1705 kilohertz.
- See Proof of Performance Measurements - The amount of frequency spectrum a radio signal occupies.
- An audio signal 960 Hz which is muted receivers announcements using the two tone frequencies of 853 and transmitted by an EAS station to actuate for interstation receipt of emergency cuing and broadcasts.
